{"title": "Toxic Twists", "author": null, "url": "https://www.poison.org/articles/toxic-twists-eye-drops", "hostname": "poison.org", "description": "Question:To appear more beautiful, women would distill this herb and drop it into their eyes. What herb was it? Answer: Don't try this at ho", "sitename": "poison.org", "date": "2012-01-01", "id": null, "license": null, "body": null, "comments": "", "commentsbody": null, "raw_text": null, "text": "Toxic Twists Eye Drops\nThe Bottom Line\nQuestion:To appear more beautiful, women would distill this herb and drop it into their eyes. What herb was it?\nAnswer: Don't try this at home! Belladonna means \"beautiful woman\" in Italian. Belladonna also is another name for deadly nightshade (Atropa belladonna). Dropping a concoction of belladonna in water into the eyes causes the pupils to get bigger. At one time, this was thought to make a woman more attractive. It certainly made it hard for her to see! Absorbing enough belladonna could cause hallucinations and seizures, too.\n[Back to questions](https://www.poison.org/articles/toxic-twists-intro)", "language": null, "image": "https://www.poison.org/-/media/images/shared/articles/2012-dec/tox-trivia-quiz-7.jpg", "pagetype": "article", "links": ["/", "https://www.poison.org/help-and-faq", "https://www.poison.org/need-immediate-assistance", "https://triage.webpoisoncontrol.org/#/exclusions", "https://www.poison.org/about-webpoisoncontrol", "https://www.poison.org/what-is-webpoisoncontrol-infographic", "https://www.poison.org/poison-prevention-by-substances", "https://www.poison.org/poison-prevention-tips-by-age", "https://www.poison.org/poison-prevention-tips-by-season", "https://www.poison.org/order-materials", "/articles/podcast", "https://www.poison.org/first-aid-for-poisonings", "https://www.poison.org/how-to-seek-help-for-poisonings", "https://www.poison.org/webpoisoncontrol-data-analysis-dashboard", "https://www.poison.org/poison-statistics-national", "https://www.poison.org